This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on improving the accuracy of image recognition using an optical neural network. It also uses the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research. 

It could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it involves the development of a neural network and improving its accuracy. 

The neural network architecture and training process may also fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the use of wavelet-like patterns to modulate the phase of optical waves may relate to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as it could potentially be used in robotic vision systems.
